  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a randomized, multicentre, and parallel clinical trial with blinded to evaluator.

      The principal hypothesis is that whole-body vibration training plus exercise improves the
      body balance and prevents falls more than only exercise training in institutionalized older
      people. The number needed of patients is 160 (80 per group).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
